ColoCALL data center is the first Ukrainian data center, which was created on March 23, 2000 by a team of enthusiasts under the leadership of Sergei Gulchuk and still continues the glorious traditions of innovation.

The company offers the following solutions:
   physical servers rental in Ukraine and Europe;
   provision of cloud services in Ukraine and Europe;
   data backup;
   other additional services.

ColoCALL data center from the very beginning to the present is:
   reliability, performance and scalability of modern solutions to meet all new customer requirements and, at the same time, to follow the proud tradition of sustainability inherent in our company at all times;
   asceticism in decisions (and this greatly affects the cost of services). Using our services you will always have the best price/performance ratio on the market;
   non-standard approach. We don’t like cliches, we always try to think for ourselves, find effective solutions and get results that are often inaccessible to others.

We are supporters of the idea that business is first and foremost people. And ColoCALL is the way all the people who were involved with it made it. At all stages of the company's development leading positions in it were occupied by real professionals, engineers, who, first of all, share an interest in the business that we do.

ONLY DATA is a tech Portuguese company focused on offering cutting-edge solutions and consultancy in (Data Engineering using Cloud (Azure,AWS and Google Cloud Platform).

Our goal is to help companies:
• Plan and migrate on-premises data to the cloud, applying best practices, monitoring, and cost optimization;
• become data-driven and extract knowledge and insights from the data using Machine Learning, Cloud, and data engineering to make smart and quick decisions;
• Plan, adopt, train, and/or mentor employees to begin to reap the benefits of Data Analysis and Machine Learning on the cloud;

Data Engineering main activities:
• Organize, ingest, cleanse, validate and transform structured or unstructured data, in batch or
streaming, for storage in a data warehouse or data lake;
• MLOps;
• DataOps;
• Provide training and mentoring in Machine Learning and Data Engineering;
• Data migration from on-premises (for instance, from SAP, Salesforce, and Oracle) to cloud;
• ETL (Extract, Transform & Load) large amount of data (in batch or streaming);
• Study the environment to propose improvements and the best solution;

Tools & Frameworks:
• Data Engineering tools: Hadoop, Databricks (Spark, Delta Live Tables, Unity Catalog, MLflow, Delta Lake, SQL, Jobs, Streaming, Autoloader, and others), Spark, ADF (Azure Data Factory), Microsoft (SSIS, SSRS, SSAS), Pentaho, Glue ETL, Data Migration Services.
Management Studio), Snowflake, dbt (Data Build Tool), T-SQL, SAS, Azure, Azure DevOps, Azure Functions, Azure Storage, Azure event-hub, Azure Key Vault, Linux, Kafka and Python;
• Agile frameworks: SCRUM and KAMBAN;
• Machine Learning tools: Azure Machine Learning Studio and Python/Spark.

